<DOC><DOCNO> AP880315-0249 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-15-88 0904EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Prudential     03-15 0152</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Prudential,0159</SECOND><HEAD>Prudential-Bache Posts $164 Million Loss In 1987</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Prudential-Bache Securities Inc. lost $164million, more than previously estimated.   Prudential Insurance Co. of America, the securities firm'sparent, said Monday its own profit from operations, beforedividends and federal income tax, rose to $2.65 billion from $2.55billion. Prudential did not announce a net income figure.   Prudential, the nation's largest insurer, did not detail thereasons for the loss at Prudential-Bache except to say it includeda charge of $47 million from the closing of an international tradeunit.   Prudential-Bache told its employees in January it had taken anunspecified charge related to litigation involving the allegedattempt by the Hunt brothers of Texas to corner the silver marketin early 1980.   The securities subsidiary also said it had taken substantialcharges hiring investment bankers and had losses in the Octoberstock market crash and its aftermath.</TEXT></DOC>